               <p>1350. <persName id="def1-1350-18350511" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1350-18350511" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1350-18350511" type="surname" value="GREEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1350-18350511" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN GREEN</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-1350-18350511" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-1350-18350511" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1350-18350511" type="age" value="16"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1350-18350511" type="surname" value="SUTTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1350-18350511" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM SUTTON</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18350511-1350-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18350511-1350-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18350511-1350-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp> stealing, on the <rs id="t18350511-cd-207" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18350511-1350-offence-1 t18350511-cd-207"></join>21st of April</rs>, 1 handkerchief, value 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of a man unknown, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350511-name-1367" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1367" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1367" type="surname" value="REARDON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1367" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>DANIEL REARDON</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 21st of April, I was on duty in Greenwich fair, about six o'clock in the evening—I saw the two prisoners in company to<lb></lb>gether—I watched them, and saw them follow a gentleman and two ladies—</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183505110218"></xptr>
               <p>Sutton drew the gentleman's handkerchief from his pocket—Green followed close to him with his hand on his shoulder—I took hold of Sutton, and he threw the handkerchief from his trowsers—I touched the gentleman, and said, "Have you lost any thing?"—he said, "No, I do not think I have," but he felt, and missed it—a crush then came on, and I lost the gentleman and ladies, but I kept Sutton—Green said that Sutton should not go with me, but I got him out of the crowd, and Green followed me down to the watch-house—I found these two snuff-boxes on Sutton—I do not know the gen<lb></lb>tleman's name.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Green's Defence.</hi> I asked him what was the matter—I followed him down to the station, and he said he would take me as one of the gang.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Sutton's Defence.</hi> I was standing, looking at a show, the officer came and took me, and asked the gentleman whether he had lost his handker<lb></lb>chief—he said, "No" several times over—I was then taken; but I never had the handkerchief in my possession.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">SUTTON—
<rs id="t18350511-1350-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18350511-1350-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-1350-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 16.—
<rs id="t18350511-1350-punishment-193" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18350511-1350-punishment-193" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
